headline: Sweep Launches Multi-Org Agent to Bring Cross-System Intelligence to Salesforce

headline: Teetering US tech trade puts anchor on market as Nvidia test looms
summary: The technology stock trade has stumbled out of the starting block in 2026, stemming from pressure from artificial intelligence disruption fears and the allure of groups that have lagged, but the broader market may struggle to make substantial gains without the ‌heavyweight sector's help.  Nvidia's quarterly report on Wednesday looms as the next test for tech, as questions are being raised about whether AI-related selloffs have been ‌too harsh and when there may be a turning point for under-pressure stocks.  The semiconductor giant and world's largest company by market capitalization is an AI bellwether, whose results and outlook could ripple widely through the ​industry.

headline: Salesforce tops Q4 earnings estimates: 2 key takeaways
summary: Salesforce (CRM) reported fourth quarter earnings results on Wednesday after the closing bell. Adjusted earnings per share (EPS) beat Wall Street's expectations, coming in at $3.81 (compared to analyst estimates of $3.05), while revenue only narrowly beat expectations at $11.2 billion (compared to analyst estimates of $11.17 billion). Salesforce's first quarter revenue outlook also modestly beat expectations. Yahoo Finance Tech Editor Dan Howley takes a closer look at the numbers with Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton, highlighting two key details investors should be paying attention to. Meanwhile, Moor Insights & Strategy founder, CEO, and chief analyst Patrick Moorhead comes on the show to explain why he thinks recent disruption in the software sector (IGV) might be overblown. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Tech Stocks Rally in Front of Nvidia Results
summary: Stocks pushed higher Wednesday, with technology shares leading a second straight day of gains as investors positioned themselves ahead of  Nvidia  closely watched earnings report.  The S&P 500’s technology sector was the day’s biggest gainer, adding 1.8%, in what was a mixed day across sectors.  The tech-heavy Nasdaq composite climbed 1.3%, while the Dow Jones Industrial Average added 308 points, or 0.6%.

headline: Salesforce Sees Stable Growth Despite Wall Street’s AI Concerns
summary: Salesforce  expects revenue to grow in the current fiscal year at about the same rate as it did the year before, as investors worry about AI’s threat to software.  Salesforce also authorized a $50 billion share buyback program, replacing all previously unused authorizations.  Salesforce is among many companies that investors have focused on in recent weeks amid concerns that artificial-intelligence models will eventually replace software companies.

headline: Salesforce Stock Drops Despite Earnings Beat. Agentforce Demand Rises.
summary: Salesforce  stock dropped Wednesday night even after the software company reported better-than-expected fourth-quarter financials.  The cloud pioneer reported fourth-quarter adjusted earnings of $3.81 a share on revenue of $11.2 billion.  Analysts surveyed by FactSet were expecting adjusted earnings of $3.05 a share on revenue of $11.19 billion.

headline: Heard on the Street Recap: Netflix and Chill
summary: What Happened in Markets Today Stock indexes climbed on Wednesday as tech and software sectors continued their recovery from Monday’s selloff. The Nasdaq composite led the charge with a 1.3% gain, while the S&P 500 and Dow Jones Industrial Average saw more modest increases of less than 1%.
